    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-07T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7014: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-08T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 8, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 8—6:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>249. Paragraph 1 of Legation’s 241, June 3, 5 p.m. Japanese have now announced
                    that equal number of troops from Tientsin garrison will not be returned to Japan
                    for the present. This is contrary to usual practice and results in substantial
                    strengthening of Tientsin garrison.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
